#

- Few things about Computing Resources:

1) CPU vs RAM 

CPU:
Measured a fraction of time
Ex: 200m(0.2cpu), 1cpu(1000m)
Compressible
Throttles
1 CPU is equal to:
1 vCPU in AWS
1 Core in GCP
1 vCore in Azure
1 Hyperthread on bare-metal

RAM:
Measured in Bytes
Ex: 1KB (1000 bytes), 1KiB (1024 bytes)
Ex: 1MB (1000 KB), 1MiB (1024 KiB)
Not Compressible
Terminates

1) Request and Limits:

Example: 
resources:
  requests:
    memory: "200Mi"
    cpu: "1"
  limits:
    memory: "2Gi"
    cpu: "1"

request how much minimum resources it need to be scheduled on any node.

limit maximum resource allocation to a pod.

Once the pod is created Resources are not allowed to change you must delete that.

Quality of Service:

This class is used to determine which pod should be deleted when resources are limited.

Limit Range Resource:

Limit range validates each pod in namespace: 
Limit range is used at container/pod level.

ex: limit-range.yaml 

Resource Quota:

Resource Quota is used to limit resources at namespace level.


